<item>
            <title>[FLUME-1322] ChannelProcessor should catch Throwable to work around close() clobbering uncaught Exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLUME-1322</link>
                <project id="12311321" key="FLUME">Flume</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ChannelProcessor currently allows channel.close() to clobber any uncaught exceptions since close() is called from within a finally block (and it has precondition checks). Catch Throwable to work around this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
